description.1: Wolverine and Sabretooth return! More surprises are revealed as Jean Grey takes Havok on a mission to save her old friend, Logan! And out for blood is the pinnacle of the Weapon X program, Sabretooth!
description.3: The First Appearance of Ultimate X-Men!  The world stands on the brink of genetic war. Mankind makes the first move, launching an army of giant, cybernetic executioners called Sentinels - programmed to target and eliminate mutants. The only force preventing total annihilation: the X-Men!
description.5: Spotlighting the living legend of WWII, Captain America! Will the star-spangled Avenger be reunited with his dead former sidekick, Bucky? Hey, anything can happen in this alternate future world of Earth X!
description.10: Secrets of Genis' past are revealed! Writer Fabian Nicieza returns to Captain Marvel for this special one-off issue that answers long-standing questions about Captain Marvel's past!
description.11: Bob Reynolds has always been the best friend of Reed Richards. As the Sentry he stood by Mr. Fantastic against Dr. Doom and traveled with him into the Negative Zone. And Reed was the best man at Bob's wedding! So if the Sentry remembers these monumental moments...why doesn't anyone else?
description.12: The Golden Guardian and the Green Goliath team up! The Hulk has been many things over the years. Rampaging, savage...even intelligent. But did you know he was once a sidekick?
description.13: The Golden Guardian and the web-slinger team up! One famous picture of the Sentry graced the covers of every major magazine and newspaper in publication. That picture was snapped by Peter Parker. Now the man who took the picuture and the man who is in the picture meet to discuss the oncoming threat of the Void!
description.14: It's the chilling conclusion to the series that has everybody talking! As the Fantastic Four, the Avengers, Dr. Strange and more of Marvel's mightiest stand firm, the Void unleashes its fury on the East Coast! Can even their combined power defeat the darkness? Or will it come down to one man and strength of a different kind?
description.15: Turns out that the Sentry has taught some hard-learned lessons to X-Man Angel in the past...
description.16: The Russian is out to get Frank. But will Spacker Dave, Joan and Mr. Bumpo be caught in the crossfire?
description.18: INFINITY'S END PART 4 The power of the Star Chamber is unleashed! Jedi Quinlan Vos loses a friend while attempting to save an entire planet from destruction. There's no light at the end of this tunnel.
description.19: Marvel Boy takes on Doctor Midas directly...with Oubliette's freedom at stake!
description.20: Cable and Jean are hot on the trail of the missing Cyclops. Too bad for Scott, so are the former Dark Rider Gauntlet and the Horseman Pestilence!
description.21: After Peter Rasputin's death, Nightcrawler needs some time away from his X-Men family.
description.22: Beast has discovered a cure for the Legacy Virus. The catch: the first mutant to use it dies!
description.26: The race is on as Han Solo and Chewie search the planet Kalkovak for information leading to the legendary Vassilika of Yavin. Things get lively, though, when hardcore bounty hunters Bossk, Dengar, and IG-88 show up with a laundry list of grudges to settle! And there's nothing more explosive than bad blood between scoundrels! Throw in a swaggering Lando Calrissian, a seductive Jozzel Moffet, and a band of curious Jawas, and you've got yourself the fixings for a visit the locals aren't too likely to forget!
description.30: We open this issue at Peter Parker's funeral. But Peter's desperately trying to escape from his coffin...
description.31: The Void, representative of Sentry's darkest impulses, returns, and is pulling those who encounter it to the precipice of madness.
description.33: Panther reunites with his childhood love - Storm of the X-Men! Will this super powered team-up reunite an alien child with their rightful guardian? Ororo and T'Challa bring the 'Storm und Drang' like never before!
description.34: Proticide lures Captain America into a deathtrap!
description.35: UNFINISHED BUSINESS! Raptor's on the loose again and with May lacking her Spider-Girl powers, May must use the help of an enemy to try and stop the villain in their tracks.
description.38: Shi'ar Emperor D'Ken's thirst for power has reached an all-time high! His eyes are now set on destroying the entire universe.
description.41: The FF are ambushed by an old enemy with a grudge as fierce as he is powerful! And this enemy can do anything that the Four can do and more, for he is...THE SUPER-SKRULL!
description.50: A UNIVERSE X spotlight on the one and only Amazing Spider-Man! An older Peter Parker is back in web-slinging form, but he's in over nhis head when he gets caught in a sinister illusion! Will Peter be able to separate dreams and reality?
description.52: Wolverine, Bullseye, the Hulk. The Punisher has faced his share of tough guys, but will he be able to survive the killer known as the Russian?
description.53: Iron Man teams up with Nick Fury to tackle a threat at the bottom of the ocean.  What terror awaits them under the sea?
description.54: It's Darkdevil Vs. the Scrier, the one who holds limitless cosmic power, in this epic finale battle!
description.55: Zey-Rogg continues his battle for vengeance against Genis, and he's got a pack of deadly Kree bloodhounds to back him up! Can Captain marvel come out on top? And whose side is Zet-Rogg's sister really on?
description.56: With Professor Xavier by his side, Bishop enters the final throes of battle against Deathbird -- usurping Shi'ar assassin and sister to Empress Lilandra!
description.57: The battle over the Legacy Virus comes to a head, and no mutant will ever be the same!
description.58: THE Green Goblin returns in Amazing Spider-Man #25, and this time rather than going head-to-head, wants Spider-Man to leave the civilian-saving behind and join him in darkness.
description.60: Continued from Mutant X #31, the end is near! One by one, the Mutant X world's most powerful heroes are falling! Only one person is capable of saving both the planet of The Six and our world. His name is Havok. Fear him. And fear for him!
description.63: The Six embark on a rescue mission to save Bloodstorm and Gambit! Outcasts leaders Dagger and Cloak aim to kill Remy, but a fellow vampire swoops in for the save. And, Hank McCoy devises a serum that forever changes the outcome for Remy and Ororo.
description.67: INFINITY'S END PART 3 The witch Ros Lai has revealed her true self to Jedi Quinlan Vos, and now she wants him dead. While Quin wants to find a way into the Star Chamber in order to stop it from being used ever again, Ros Lai needs to activate the Chamber's power in order to kill her wicked mother, the witch Zalem. Either way, it looks like Quin is going to have to deal with a whole mess of angry witches before his job will be finished!
description.68: Where can you find an encounter between'Yoda'and a'probe droid'onDagobah, the chance meeting of'C-3PO'and'Darth Vader'on'Cloud City, and a cannonball by'Boba Fett'into the'Sarlacc'on'Tatooine? In the many pages of'Star Wars Tales'#6, the ultimate romp through a'galaxy far, far away'!
description.69: Five years before the events of'Episode I,'Jedi'Master'Qui-Gon Jinn'and his apprentice,'Obi-Wan Kenobi, are already legendary for their exploits. When a valuable cargo freighter fails to reach its destination on the planet Coruscant, Qui-Gon and Obi-Wan are sent into deep space to search for the missing ship. Their investigation leads them to the distant, lawless world of'Ord Mantell, where everyone carries a grudge and a'blaster, and Jedi are less than welcome. Despite their powers, the Jedi soon realize that it will take more than'the Force'and'lightsabers'to survive!
description.71: Remember when Han Solo was still a scoundrel? Ah, the good ol' days... A group of Hutts decide to place a wager to see who really carries the most weight throughout the Galactic Underworld. When it comes to setting a goal for this contest they decide to hire crews to seek out the fabled Yavin Vassilika-a legendary treasure which most sentient beings believe to be fictional. The best and brightest rogues of the Star Wars universe are recruited, and you won't want to miss it as Boba Fett, Han Solo, Chewbacca, Greedo, Lando, Dengar, and others team up and square off to decide who is the best scoundrel in the galaxy!
description.78: Spider-Man uncovers the plot by Senator Ward to transfer the pathogen which has become too much on his body.
description.80: Wrapped in steel and scoured by swirling sands of time, this sweeping saga of exotic locales and explosive action will at last fill in the gap between the events of FANTASTIC FOUR #25 and issue #30, and fully explore the inner workings of one of Marvel's most captivating characters -- Doctor Doom!
description.81: As Marvel Boy and Oubliette reminisce on their past, Doctor Midas continues his search for Noh-Varr's ship.
description.84: Spider-Man digs deep and discovers that he may have met Sentry once before...but under what circumstances?
description.85: It's a Maximum Security tie-in! Agent Ross heads to the Wakandan Resurrection Altar to revive the cast member who was struck down last issue, but he's not the only one interested in its power! It seems some alien prisoners incarcerated on Earth see it as their way off this mudball! But is there even a Black Panther to stand against these otherworldly invaders?
description.86: Extra-dimensional creatures have attacked Connie Ferrari. Can Cap save her before it's too late?
description.87: Normie and May go head-to-head to end the war between their two families, "as soon as one dies." Who will fall?
description.89: It's the X-Men vs. the Shi'ar Imperial Guard to rescue Lilandra! But even if they succeed, can they hope to stop Emperor D'Ken's scheme of gaining absolute power with the M'Kraan crystal?
description.92: Diablo triumphant! Last issue the evil alchemist laid the smackdown on the Fantastic Four and things haven't improved for Marvel's first family! What is the source of Diablo's newfound power? Will the Deacon be enough to turn the tide of battle? And just what does the Gideon Trust have to do with all of this?
description.95: Get ready for the stunning conclusion to the most epic X-Man adventure yet! It's the tale that will change Nate Grey's life and the course of his future forever!
description.97: The shocking conclusion that sets up AMAZING SPIDER-MAN #25 and PETER PARKER, SPIDER-MAN #25! Over the years, Spider-Man has defeated Norman Osborn again and again... now the winning streak ends! At long last, the Green Goblin stands triumphant!
description.98: He's big, he's bad, and he's Bolshevik! He's the Russian, and he's been brought in by Ma Gnucci to squash the Punisher! But he'd better hurry, because it's moving day for Frank Castle. How do his neighbors feel about this?
description.99: Iron Man becomes embroiled in the Fantastic Four's conflict with Ego, the Living Planet. The Silver Surfer returns!

0.text: In 1961, a quartet of intrepid explorers rocketed into space, were bathed in mysterious Cosmic Rays, and were transformed into the fabulous Fantastic Four! Mr. Fantastic, brilliant inventor with an elastic body! Invisible Woman, master of force fields! Human Torch, flaming hotshot! The Thing, monstrous man of might! In the years that have followed, this dynamic nuclear family has challenged the unknown, saving our world multiple times from the threat of alien invaders, scientists gone mad, and other-dimensional despots! Now writer/artist Erik Larsen and a host of terrific talents ask "What if Stan Lee and Jack Kirby concluded their historic run on FF with one last wild adventure?" The answer begins at the world famous Baxter Building, home of our famous foursome, which is pillaged and looted by none other than the team's arch-nemesis, Dr. Doom! What is the man in the iron mask looking for? And what does the Mad Thinker have to do with all this?

2.text: Here's what Daredevil and Spider-Man know: someone just tried to kill Wilson Fisk. Here's what we know: a revamped Gladiator and Stilt-Man are in on the hit, but a third villain is calling the shots. And by the end of this issue we'll all know the true face of the man gunning for the Kingpin!

3.text: The world stands on the brink of genetic war. Mankind makes the first move, launching an army of giant, cybernetic executioners called Sentinels - programmed to target and eliminate mutants. The only force preventing total annihilation: the X-Men!

4.text:
Daredevil, Black Widow and Moon Knight have been sucked into the
demented darkness that is Cloak. Can Dr. Strange and Shang Chi rescue
their missing teammates? And will Dagger bring herself to fight against
her former partner?

Daredevil, Black Widow and Moon Knight have been sucked into the demented darkness that is Cloak. Can Dr. Strange and Shang Chi rescue their missing teammates? And will Dagger bring herself to fight against her former partner?

5.text: Spotlighting the living legend of WWII, Captain America! Will the star-spangled Avenger be reunited with his dead former sidekick, Bucky? Hey, anything can happen in this alternate future world of Earth X!

6.text: Russian Warborgs are sent to the United States to cleanse sleeper agents of implanted memories, and X-Force is on the offense! The race is on to cure Warpath of the poison coursing through his veins!

8.text: To free his friends and countrymen, Thor must find something called the Gem of Infinite Sons. But there are those who stand in his way and they aim to do major bodily harm to the God of Thunder!

9.text: Stark meets up with an old friend whose intentions may not be what they seem...

17.text: Cable reels from the death of Moira MacTaggert.

23.text: The Hulk confronts the Abomination! The last time the Green Goliath confronted Emil Blonsky, we saw him walk away. But can the Hulk forgive the man responsible for his wife's death that easily? Especially since he's now come face-to-face with Betty's cryogenically-preserved body?

24.text: As an attempt to fool the enemy, Natasha Romanoff undergoes a procedure to look like her nemesis Yelena Belova. Unbeknownst to the Black Widow, Yelena seems to have a similar trick up her sleeve.

27.text: Spider-Man confronts the killer of a beloved family member and is shocked to discover their identity.  Plus, a Goblin is on the loose! What does this mean for Spider-Man?

28.text: CRUEL SUMMER Part 3! Wade betrayed! Deadpool's closest allies reveal their ulterior motives!

32.text: The heroes race to save the future in the world known as UNIVERSE X.

36.text: History of the relationship between Professor X and Moira MacTaggert
History of the relationship between Professor X and Moira MacTaggert

37.text: A Yakuza boss becomes Wolverine's latest adversary in his quest to rescue Amiko (again)!

39.text: Joe Fixit: a soldier for the Chicago mob?! What do these goodfellas want with the grey guy? And how does it all connect to the twisted and embarrassing secret of the enforcer named Nobby Stiles?

40.text: The Thunderbolts travel to Titan to help their comrade Moonstone with her personal issues.

42.text: THE RETURN OF K’UN-LUN PART 3 Junzo Muto, young leader of The Hand, empowered with the Iron Fist force! After stealing Daniel Rand’s inner chi, Muto seems well on his way to becoming the new leader of K’un-Lun/Tokyo. But when Wolverine and Earth’s Mightiest break the mystic barriers between themselves and Muto, all bets are off! Will Iron Fist and Misty Knight be rescued at long last?

43.text: At long last...Gambit vs. New Son!

44.text: Rogue fights a fierce battle to save Gateway from the Shadow King!

45.text: The Fantastic Four encounter one of their strangest dilemmas yet - Galactus, dead in the middle of New York City!

46.text:
Has Cloak gone bad? That question is answered as the Marvel Knights and
special guest star Dr. Strange finally confront Dagger's former partner.
Will Cloak revert back to form or will he turn out the lights on the
Knights?

Has Cloak gone bad? That question is answered as the Marvel Knights and special guest star Dr. Strange finally confront Dagger's former partner. Will Cloak revert back to form or will he turn out the lights on the Knights?

48.text: The aftermath in San Francisco following the mutagenic riots from Dr. Niles Roman have led to public outcries and mediated outbursts against mutants by people once more in fear with the effects of the city's reconstruction. Meltdown has a heart-to-heart with Cannonball, Domino rejoins the old team after their takedown of Marcus Tsung, Valentina Rychenko resurfaces to destroy a Cold War weapon systems, and the sly Dr. Rancal turns a child's parents into monstrosities...

50.text: A UNIVERSE X spotlight on the one and only Amazing Spider-Man! An older Peter Parker is back in web-slinging form, but he's in over his head when he gets caught in a sinister illusion! Will Peter be able to separate dreams and reality?

51.text: Thor, Beta Ray Bill, and the Warriors Three head to Asgard to thwart the horror of the Cask of Ancient Winters!

59.text: While the team is in New York City, Jono meets a deaf girl that he can communicate with telepathically. He likes her, but is wary of being in any kind of relationship as a mutant.

61.text: Wolverine hits New York to investigate an important murder and kidnapping mystery...

62.text: The teenaged X-Men are back at it again, this time against mutant pop sensation, Dazzler!

64.text: Spider-Man and Daredevil are friends. Daredevil knows that Spider-Man is Peter Parker. And Spider-Man knows Matt Murdock is Daredevil. Now both heroes find themselves caught at the crossroads of their vengeance, forced into the position of protecting the Kingpin of Crime from an enemy they never imagined.

65.text: What ends will Matt Murdock go to in order to retrieve the staff of his late mentor Stick? From the mean streets of New York City's Hell's Kitchen to the neon spires of Tokyo, this breakneck paced story not only touches on plot points from Frank Miller's Daredevil run, but also brings events full circle to Kevin Smith's "Guardian Devil" saga!

66.text: Belasco's plans come to fruition! The necessary souls are collected and the portal between dimensions is almost open! And as the Bloodstones are at last gathered, Thunderbird and Wolverine fight for the lives of the X-Men! Will Magik be the team's savior or their executioner? And just who is she anyway?

70.text: Belasco is close to finishing his collection of Bloodstones! Wolverine and Thunderbird battle in Limbo! Colossus and Beast face off against the N'Garai known as Pilgrim! And, on top of all that, Nightcrawler fights Magik in a winner-take-all brawl for his soul! Clues to the identity of this sword-swinging mystery woman begin to unravel this issue as the stakes continue to climb for the remaining X-Men!

73.text: Captain America and Captain Mar-Vell head to both the Savage Land and Limbo in an effort to locate the power sources of Earth X. It's the two Captains versus Space Phantoms, Dire Wraiths, and the demon called Belasco!

75.text: The last X-Man has finally returned to the present - but he's not alone! By his side is the X-Men's mentor, Professor X! On an abandoned space station, the two X-Men reunite for the fight of their lives against the Shi'ar assassin known as Deathbird! Will their combined prowess be enough to stop her murderous rampage?

76.text: Tragedy strikes the Parker household as Peter loses someone very important to him.  And find out why Peter blames himself for their death!

77.text: With Sith Lord Darth Sidious' master plan for the overthrow of the Republicin jeopardy, Sidious' apprentice and enforcer Darth Maul has cut his way through the ranks of the galactic crime syndicate Black Sun, and now there is only one barrier left between Maul and Black Sun's total destruction. Maul must go toe-to-toe with the personal bodyguards of Black Sun's top lieutenants before he can reach the pinnacle of their organization! It's Black Sun vs. the dark side, and the winner takes all!

79.text: CRUEL SUMMER Part 2! Deadpool continues his bloody mission to kill the mob bosses! Also is love in the air for the Regenerating Degenerate?

83.text: A Maximum Security tie-in! Spider-Man: abducted by aliens?! Peter Parker becomes an unwilling subject of an experiment that unleashes a horror on New York City!

88.text: The only thing standing between a legion of the Mole Man's subterranean creatures and the unwitting populace of New York City is the unlikely duo of Wolverine and Spider-Man! But what is the greater threat that looms over both sides?

90.text: Joe Fixit makes his way to Chicago...and accidentally ignites a turf war!

91.text: Scourge is back, and his grudge against the Thunderbolts is deadlier than ever! How will the T-Bolts stand up to his renewed onslaught? And where has Moonstone vanished to during this crisis?

93.text: Chang Chi battles his evil father's personal assasin.  And surprise guest stars - the Fantastic Four!

94.text: The X-Men's mission to break into Ronan's lair is tougher than any of them imagined, even with the return of Bishop! One hope still remains, as Rogue enlists the help and powers of an old friend and rival--Carol Danvers, A.K.A. Warbird!

96.text: Thor and the Avengers take some time off only to be attacked by...Galactic Patrol agents? Plus, the return of Beta Ray Bill!
